quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,31,"And He taught Adam the names - all of them. Then He showed them to the angels and said, "
  2,32,"They said, ",footnotes:1:[Whose eternal and absolute knowledge encompasses the truth and essence of all things, seen or unseen, present or absent, neither preceded by ignorance nor followed by forgetfulness.],footnotes:2:[Whose wisdom includes precise and perfect knowledge of all realities and outcomes, according to which He decrees and causes various circumstances and occurrences.]
  2,33,"He said, "
